<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Only found in a few localities in southern Greenland. Generally distributed in warm and cold temperate Europe with a few records from subarctic Norway and Finland and missing in southern Europe. The Greenland records fit well with the European records, the records from southern Greenland (Paamiut, 62.01) being the northernmost hitherto found.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
